        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: add timeout to scp spawn to prevent hanging in sandbox media staging",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where `scpFile()` spawns an scp child process with no timeout, causing hung processes and Promise leaks.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdd a 30-second `SCP_TIMEOUT_MS` with `SIGKILL` and Promise rejection. A `settled` flag prevents double-resolution.\n\n## User Impact\n\nPrevents hung SCP operations from leaking resources during remote sandbox media staging.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```\nsrc/auto-reply/reply.stage-sandbox-media.scp-remote-path.test.ts\nTest Files  1 passed (1)\n     Tests  5 passed (5)\n[test] passed 1 Vitest shard in 14.29s\n```\n\nTimeout pattern follows `src/crestodian/probes.ts` for local command probing.",
